						               													<description>Our climate is changing and the elements that prevail in the forest are unstable. We experience this by dealing with the effects of violent weather phenomena such as: drought, storm or heavy rainfall. We have no direct influence on them, but we can predict the effects they cause and try to prevent them. We can counteract some of these changes, others need to be adapted to.  The way we manage water and how we protect forests against fires is crucial in adapting forests to climate changes.  Keeping forests in good condition is your task now.&amp;#10;It is your decisions and your actions that determine whether you manage the elements of fire and water.&amp;#10;&amp;quot;&amp;#197;&amp;#187;ywio&amp;#197;&amp;#130;y Lasu&amp;quot; is an original board game designed to be played individually among several people. The game balances the aspect of luck and the impact of player's decisions on the course of the game. Clear and intuitive rules allow you to quickly feel the vibe of the game regardless of age or experience with board games. Protect your forest from the effects of the forces of the elements, be ready for possible disasters and make sure the forest lasts longer for the benefit of people and nature.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each round, players simultaneously pick the card with action which they will perform on the board and then pass the cards to the next player. The action is to place their marker in one of the forest zones: red, blue or neutral respectively.  At the end of the game, after an appropriate number of rounds, the players gain points for the advantages in the regions or the proper arrangement of their markers in relation to each other and the selected cards during the game. The winner is the player who collects the most points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
